My burrito, especially the carnitas and the burrito, was incroyable!
Best nachos and queso in the Bay area!
Really good food price is a little pricy though
One of the best restaurants in the Bay Area. Simply incredible.
Fine food. Veggie burrito a delight. Reasonsble prices. Be well.
Superb food! The Coca cola beef is bomb and the ceviche is fresh and tasty. Do not pass this place up
Thought it would be better

The food is pretty fantastical honestly, reasonably priced and with reasonable sizes. I personally prefer to get extra salsa and cheese since the food can be a little dry/plain, but I think that is largely because of the high quality ingredients and lack of lard/fat.
One of my favorite places to get a Chile relleno.

Full disclosure: I need to come here more. Is that full disclosure worthy? 🤷‍♀️ The real is that everything I've had here is delicious, but, no disrespect to the food (what a restaurant should be known for), they have margaritas better …

I loved this place for many years. The quality and consistency has shifted as of late. Salsa is a little thinner than it used to be etc... You might think that people don’t notice cause they don’t say anything. Don’t forget what made you great in the first place ...

This spot has a great set up for outdoor dining with a large second floor patio and also seating below with heat lamps. The menu is pretty limited but I can live off their Chile Rellenos. Also so siked for the other pop up food offerings in the space.
The food was good but the service is not great. We had a very cold welcome  and all the tables were dirty. Love the atmosphere and margs were on fleek!
Really enjoyed the new location of doña. Great food, awesome patio.

Loved the pescado and carnitas tacos. Carnitas was probably the best one. Barbacoa taco was good but not as good as the other two. The churros were great too and we loved both chocolate dipping sauces it came with. My friends got the fish …

The best margaritas ever!! After enjoying a margarita to go with my veggie taco and doña ensalada, I went back to get a pitcher to take home. Amazing gluten free and vegetarian options! Two-level patio made it easy to find a table. One of my new go-to Piedmont spots.
I just by to meet someone but the outside looks very inviting.  I WILL be back.
Great spot for a quick bite with outdoor seating.  Not much for kids. I really wish they had sopa de lima (chicken soup) without heat for kids. It is great soup but too spicy for toddlers.
Love it. Great food, and the new locations deck is amazing.

Their fish tacos 😋...their chocolate chip cookies 😋...their guac and chips 😋. Because the fish tacos and chocolate chip cookies are so bomb I would trust that other items on their menu are delicious as well! One day I will venture out and try something else but I'm content with my go to! Try em' out! Enjoy!

I wasn't at Dona, ww where at Pomellas, ohhh, it was sooo good, always is! Best Middle Eastern food around, not too expensive! Mica, made a Meyer Lemon Panna Cotta..... to die for & si seasonal ,we loved it.
Super fast service for take out. Great food. Hot and fresh.
Really good bowls and drinks (sangria and iced tea) outside seating area with sun.
Delicious burritos and strong drinks. What more do you want?
My veggie burrito was so delicious and flavorful. It made my afternoon. Don’t forget to try the house fermented hot sauce. YUM!
First visit, just a pitstop for a snack, and totally LOVE the nacho cheese dip and chips, amazing spicey deliciousness. Jim Bob says, check it out.
Just bought carnitas burrito. Very good and large portions! Smart idea to give good deal. Those that are cheap will lose good customers!
(Translated by Google) Excellent customer service  (Original) Excelente servicio al cliente
Dona makes great all around Mexican food good. Love the tacos especially.....love the vegetarian tacos. Great location.
veggie burrito is phenomenal

Love the place and when we eat there everything is perfect. But I often pick up between 7:30 and 8 (just before closing) on the way home. It looks like they don't give the same amount of love to those dishes. I have gotten stale tortillas …
Best burrito on the street.
I love absolutely everything about doña!  The queso is crave worthy, the cocktails are amazing, I need a doña burrito once a week!  Do yourself a favor and get in there!

Normally I’d give them 5 stars but today I tried the outdoor dining. I was so excited to have the Pescado bowl which is only good fresh. Unfortunately they don’t tell you that they won’t notify you when your food is ready. After waiting for …
Just came in today. A tiny enchilada, margarita, nachos, and sparkling water all for $40.. I had to feed my fiancé after we came here.. could have went to chipotle dude
Great prices, solid food and the upstairs is open and sunny. Barbacoa bowl or tacos are my go to but the fish and chicken are just as good.
Serving from walkup window.  Large areas for outside dining including upstair balconies.  Service was quick.  Great fish tacos but everything looked good.
Consistent take out, good portions. If you order mixed drinks to go, make sure to check. They add that during pickup to keep the food hot/drink cold and sometimes forget to add it.
Sorry to tell you it is closed forever, it did before Corona Virus Shutdown. Please stop asking how I liked it when I visit my girlfriend's apartment in that building.
Great options, can make lots of things on the menu vegan. Great venue. Easy pick up system. Great outdoor seating!
I love their drinks and chile rellenos!!
The food is excellent.

So excited they are open for pick-up! Food carefully packaged in compostable containers (nice!). I appreciated the minor  tweaks they made to make their dishes even better for take out. The chicken enchiladas, chile rellano, and ceviche were as delicious as always.
Awesome food
Top notch. Fish taco is beyond.  Everything is. Salsa de arbol? OMFGGGG! House made cookies?  So effin good.

Constructive critique:  -Great take-out/pickup system -Undercooked rice (easy fix) -Throw in extra hot sauce/salsa with take-out orders -Pico de Gallo needs a bit more kick and cilantro -Beans need a touch more flavor (are you using epazote?)  Almost there. Looking forward to seeing you all succeed.
Very good

First, let's continue to care for our families, friends, and neighbors by staying at home and, when appropriate, ordering meal deliveries from local restaurants.  Dona is a Piedmont Ave treasure!  Excellent food, lovely staff, and confirm …
Fantastic food, excellent drink choices, casual, cheery atmosphere and outdoor seating.
It was very good. The civechi was awesome. The burrito was a pass. Want to try it again.
Best queso I've had in California. Their kale and squash bowl is great.

Was curious about this place because I love Doña Tomás. The food here is quality from an ingredient perspective, but not very creative, and the space doesn't have enough decor to give it a full personality yet. I think they're still getting things together, hopefully it will improve in the coming months.

Tona is the new iteration of DonaTomas, which is used to be in Temescal.  Dona is more like Tacubaya (their sister restaurant) on 4th Street Berkeley.  Food is excellent, no table service, and well worth the visit.  The menus are different …
Good drinks and the foods not that bad. my favorite is the queso with chips and the Barbacoa tacos or burrito is good.

Excellent food. We were fans back on telegraph, when the restaurant was table-service oriented They have changed location, changed to counter service, and the result is a more budget-friendly but nearly identical food experience.  The tacos …
Descent food, but parking is always a nightmare in Piedmont.
Amazing food and drinks, very kind, fast service. The noise reduction needs work, but it's a wonderful place if you don't mind shouting a little when it's full!
Amazing place every dish is amazing. Great drinks. Glad they moved to Piedmont Ave.

Sat at the bar for my first visit. Friendly & attentive service, good tequila/mezcal selection and -based cocktail menu. Only ordered a snack (the plátanos), but they were tasty. A welcome addition to the peri-Kaiser/lower Piedmont block, …
Really delicious upscale Mexican food. Can't wait to go back and try a cocktail or two!

Nice open space that looks like it would be good for groups. Order at the counter type, with ample seating. The tuna ceviche tostaditos were really tasty, a little pricey at $13. The butternut squash and kale filling was really good in the burrito. They also have happy hour deals of $2 off some items on the menu.

Nice food, super fast service, good atmosphere. It's a place where you order at a counter and then find your own seating. They brought out our food almost as soon as I sat down. It was pretty tasty and decently sized for $4.25 per taco. I'd come back for the churros when I feel like treating myself!

Plant-based menu isn't up to par with 2019 or the Bay area. People that don't eat dairy are not interested in having half of the ingredients removed from an item in order to be able to eat it. Not very thoughtful. The space looks really nice though.

Amazingly tasty food! It’s a whole New Mexican food experience! The simple chicken quesadilla was heavenly the first time I went, and today the sopa de Lima was out of this world! The broth was so flavorful, they must have cooked those …
Tasty. Counter service. Full bar. A little loud.
Incredible food, plenty of elbow room for groups. Parking! A+

Finally a proper Mexican restaurant on the ave!  Flavorful food all around - homemade tortillas, the beans are perfectly cooked, tasty churros for dessert and they even are able to make a Mexican hot chocolate with oat milk (swoon!) The cocktails are delicious too. Plenty of reasons to give this place a try.

Over priced for the quality. Carnitas tacos were very dry and the salsa on top was composed of mediocre tomatoes that had the texture of Roma tomatoes. Soupa de Lima was mediocre to fair, but definitely not living up to its price point. …
$10 for some chips and 1/4 cup of guac..... Pollo Asado was super dry Guac tasted good

It’s a great day when your favourite local restaurant reinvents itself and the prices have somehow gone down! The chile relleno is still on the menu and absolutely perfect. Many gluten free options and staff is aware of cross contamination. We will be back again and again.
Great food, great drink's.
Their burritos 🌯 taste how love feels♥️
Good food, lively cheerful + casual atmosphere.
Best brunch in Temescal. Sad to see you go!
Adorable place, good food, not overly loud or busy.
My girlfriend and I just came here and we had a delicious meal of carnitas and mole enchiladas. We are absolutely stuffed but we will be coming back many times. Wonderful experience overall!!
The Molé is amazing. Some of the best Chile Rellenos I've ever had, and I have had a lot in my lifetime.  The Ceviché is to die for!
Really tasty but a bit spendy for small portions. Love the atmosphere!!! Great outdoor space too.
Went there for the Margaritas per the reviews and I was not too impressed but I had a great soup and overall was good
Food is mediocre drinks are a little bit better, but I hear it's closing down soon.
Delicious food patio dining reasonably priced highly recommended
Awsome
I love the patio and the food! It’s a really great lunch spot. The patio is dog friendly.
Bomb food. Enchellada a bit dry.
Excellent food, friendly service!
Ate outside, had the lime soup(great) and the salad(fantastic). Would eat again.

I always come for the Margaritas, tacos and guac. I love the bartenders and sit at the bar during Happy Hour. I hate that they're closing shop and moving to a new location at the end of summer where the parking is worse. But I've got nothing but love for this spot and the bartenders - thanks Mariah!🍹
Visit Sophie at the bar! And be sure to go before they close after 30 years at the end of 2019. They're opening a new counter service spot in a new location after that.

Food was ok nothing worth returning for. The horchata was ok not the best I've ever eat. The tacos were alright. Not that amazing. Overpriced for sure. And tons of stuck up patrons. Not my give not price range. Def won't be back.
Amazing food and drink
If you're not worried about price, and you care more about the appearance of your food then the taste, this would be a great place for you.  On a side note it's not really Mexican
Great margaritas, but otherwise just a step above your normal Mexican place. My dinner was gritty like maybe the greens in the meal hadn't been cleaned enough.
Solid, inventive, Central American dishes and drinks. Some drinks, like the one with worcestershire sauce, are a bit much but the variations of tequila and mezcal are wonderful.
Great food!

Love Doña Tomas. It's my favorite restaurant in Oakland and I went tonight because I learned that it's closing. A version will revive on Piedmont, but I've had so many good times here that it will be sorely missed. They close in August so get your butt there while.you still can.
Great food and drinks
Delicious and cozy
Excellent food and drinks - the menu is short and seasonal. Don't miss the carnitas and camote. Seriously.
Always so fun
Always great foods and service
Carnitaa are AMAZING.
So fun. Sit outside in the back! And the chilaquiles verde were incredible

So, I grew up next to the border and I absolutely love Mexican Food. I don’t like this place. I feel like the food is overpriced and the staff pretentious. Not my thing. That said, I could also see that the ingredients used were top notch …
Delicious brunch at a reasonable price for the quality. Will definitely go back.

Fantastic every time! Last night's dinner was the Sopa de Lima (chicken lime soup) and guacamole with totopos - couldn't have been better! The winter crud had set in and there's no better cure than that soup. A huge portion is served …
Great for brunch and when you’re finished eating, head over to Temescal alley for shopping or ice cream!

Food excellent. We showed up at end of brunch service (not knowing this, was a spontaneous act as we passed by), and they sat us but then an employee let us know we came in at end of service and they shouldn't have sat us. Left a bad taste. If you sit us then don't try and cause us to feel bad. Otherwise great food and server was great.
Not authentic Mexican food

Only had breakfast but very tasty. Prices are typical for Oakland. Definitely worth a visit. One negative that hopefully won't be repeated  Last time there was hair in my food. It was replaced, although they didn't ask me if I wanted it …
Delicious

If you like Mexican food, go here. If you are not enthusiastic about Mexican food, but your SO is, then also go here - you will be ok. Fast service, friendly staff (although they are not really very good, or at least they don’t seem to be …
We had the carne asada, Chile relleno, and ahi civiche tuna tacos! Everything was delicious! Left very full!

(Translated by Google) It is a good restaurant with good service, and although the food is delicious, it does not taste like Mexico.  (Original) Es un buen restaurante con buen servicio, y aunque la comida es rica no sabe a México.

Not cheap, but worth the price.  The owner is in our local business improvement group and we have been there for meetings many times.  This is also a great place for out-of-town visitors and other important guests.  Great date night place. …

Decent Mexican food, like grandma would have made if she were a gringa. Don't get me wrong, it's way more authentic than most, but how come they don't have tasty house salsas? I mainly come for the brunch chilaquiles. The hostess had RBF and seemed so annoyed at everyone the last time I was here.

Fantastic food and reasonably priced drinks but I’ve had a terrible time with their service. I was double charged (one of my charges was over +$100) and their servers were too busy to pick up. After a while, my calls were being directed …
Excellent brunch fare for a reasonable price.
The Best Carnitas I have ever tasted!
Perfect place for a Sunday brunch. Great, flavorful authentic mexican food. Mole is to die for. All good. Hella good place.
Excellent chilaquiles and a great Sopa de Lima!
The best happy hour and Rosie is awesome!

The atmosphere and servers were great. The food itself was bland and unimpressive. Churros were delicious.  We ordered the chilaquiles verdes & carnitas Hash. Coconut horchata iced coffee was watered down or just flavorless.
Pretty good food. Nice place, music not very complimentary to ambiance, and type of restaurant. Liked the mole enchiladas and the Chile rellenos.
Delicious Mexican food. Way over priced. Close by taquerias might be better options for the price but will not have the classy ambiance, mezcal menu, or delightful service.

This place is charming and the service is consistently good. In nice weather, the courtyard is a wonderful place to relax and eat.  Unfortunately, while the food is well prepared, it is also pretty gringo-ized. Everything seems to have …
Some the best Mexican food in the East Bay. Great scratch bar, as well.
Excellent food and service.  Wonderful ambiance, with extensive our seating in the patio.
So delicious!
Friendly down home staff with delightful food. Carnitas.
Best mole in town,  great service. I come here frequently and always enjoy it. Good drinks... good food. I always sit at tbe bar, and the bartenders are awesome :-)

Great food and atmosphere. The only negative side was the service - we had a hard time getting ahold of our waiter. Great tequila and mezcal selection though and the menu had a lot of great options.  I’m looking forward to going back :)
Excellent upscale Mexican food with cocktails that highlight tequila and mescal.
Great brunch. I love the huevos revueltos and guacamole. Their bloody Maria is excellent. Definitely worth a stop.
Great cocktails. Great food
Great food, lot of options for veggies and meat, quality drinks in a loud but good setting.
Superb Bloody Mary!
Tasty restaurant with a super cool outdoor seating area in the back.

Probably the best Mexican food I have had in the US in several years. Spread out over two rooms separated by a hallway, this bustling and vibrant restaurant features high-quality fresh ingredients in intensely flavorful dishes. The portion …

I've liked this place as a semi-splurge spot for years.  Ingredients are fresh, most dinner dishes are delish.  I'm not sure the brunch is worth the price for me, but dinner absolutely is.  Their recent lunch service is basic, but tasty.  I …

If you're going for breakfast, try the huevos rancheros with some fresh guacamole and thick, crispy chips. For a cocktail, I'd recommend the Celorita that's made with habañero infused  mezcal.  Parking is street only so plan to give yourself some time if you have reservations.
Yummy !!!

Everything we ate here was amazingly delicious, and the service was very friendly and prompt. I can't recommend this place more! The camarones tacos are awesome, as is the ceviche tostada appetizer. It's pretty pricey, but it is the Bay Area after all, and this stuff is legit.
Great Mexican food and fun venue. The drinks are also quite delicious. Carnitas is the classic but they have many other good options
One of the best mex restaurants ever.  Not a burrito place, but the awesome mex food that reminds me of Mexico City. Try the carnita, or the amazing chili relleno
Great place for mornings, never much of a line.
Great margaritas  and good food
Good Mexican food, but overpriced.
Best margaritas & bartenders around. Also, the Happy Hour menu is great. Guac & chips are my favs.
Very tasty food that is authentic but unassuming.
Delicious, innovative, beautiful!
Delicious and a much larger restaurant than the pix might suggest. Patio seating was perfect.

Oaxaca on a plate! Although the menu doesn't include the traditional chapulines (grasshoppers) and iguana on offer in the Pacific Coastal Mexican state of Oaxaca, the food satisfies a certain nostalgia for that place. Anytime an occasion …
Great Mexican food and cocktails.
Liked the atmosphere and loved the food!
Great drinks, authentic, fresh food. The salsa is VERY special.
nice for brunch
Delicious braised lamb, awesome cocktails, beautiful ceviche.
Went here for a B-day brunch - the Bloody Maria is AMAZING. But the prices are a bit high.
Lamb chili verde! Mezcal Margueritas! OMFG
Great food and service. The only drawback is that it can be unbelievably loud and hard to have a normal conversation depending on where you are seated.

The food here is always really good, and the menu has interesting modern Mexican cuisine alongside some typical standards.  I really love the back yard area - give the place a comfortable homey vibe in the midst of the hipness surrounding it.
A favorite, always excellent.

Honestly some of the best brunch available in the area. Outdoor seating when it's nice, a wide variety of interesting dishes that sit happily between modern Mexican cuisine and brunch classics. All the dishes are a perfect single serving - …

I want to like this place more: the patio, the bars and the cocktails are great! But the food just isn't flavorful enough to match the prices in my opinion. Still, will keep going again and again for their happy hour
Good margaritas, OK guac, quality food. Excellent patio seating.

Maybe a bad day/too busy Friday evening, but had higher expectations than what was delivered. Ceviche was so and so and served with warm plates (straight out of the dishwasher?). Wanted at least some spiciness to the chille relleno. Great margarita. Servers were friendly.
There's only one dish I eat here, but it's one of my favorite meals in existence. Get the Carnitas!
The food is so fresh here.  We've never had a bad meal.  One of my favorite things here is Budin corn and zucchini pudding.
Fantastic, and wholly authentic Mexican cuisine available in extremely few places in the bay area, starting with their home made from scratch salsas.  Make a reservation as it fills up.

Great cocktails,  Nice atmosphere.  Very popular so it gets noisy.  If that's a problem sit out in the patio, which is very nice.  This is upscale Mexican so you won't find burritos on the menu.  The food is interesting.
Upscale Mexican cuisine, a rarity in Oakland.
A really nice spot for brunch.  The huevos were light and delicious.  The patio was sunny and warm.  Will be back.
My favorites: carnitas, ceviche, and refried beans. I wish they'd bring back the refried navy bean dish they used to do with pork lard. Great drinks too.
Best fancy Mexican in the bay.

A mexican place trying to be gourmet. They just don't quite make it good or unique enough to justify their pricing. More like eating average mexican food from fancy plates with mid-high end service. Don't see the return on the investment after a few visits.
the waiters are very nice. the food is very high concept. it's delicious, but it's also strange. take people you want to impress with your cosmopolitan ways.
love the patio on a warm night.
Great margaritas, great chips & salsa. Everything was fab including the Oakland Hipster scene in full effect.  Servers had great knowledge about allergy info as well (including Gluten-free).
great mexican smells upon entering.
it's look great -- like a trip to  the real mexico.
